\u0435\u0442\u0430.ru |date=2017-12-12|accessdate=2018-05-25}}</ref>\n*[[Sergei Polonsky]]{{refn|group=b|name=Polonsky|Sergey Polonsky received Cambodian citizenship in 2013. Due to [[2020 amendments to the Constitution of Russia|amendments to the Constitution]], if adopted by [[2020 Russian constitutional referendum|2020 referendum]], he can't run for President, because one of the amendments bans foreign citizenship.}}, businessman, former CEO of the Mirax Group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mk.ru/politics/2018/01/11/polonskiy-nameren-pobedit-v-prezidentskoy-gonke-v-2024-godu.html |title=\u041f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043d\u0430\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043d \u043f\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0432 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u043e\u043d\u043a\u0435 \u0432 2024 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0443 |publisher=Mk.ru |date= |accessdate=2018-03-22}}</ref>\n*[[Boris Yakemenko]], public activist and founder of the [[Nashi (youth movement)|Nashi]] movement.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ria.ru/election2018_news/20180106/1512192704.html |title=\u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441 \u042f\u043a\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e \u0437\u0430\u044f\u0432\u0438\u043b \u043e \u0432\u044b\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0435 \u0438\u0437 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u043e\u043d\u043a\u0438 |publisher=Ria.ru |date= |accessdate=2018-03-22}}</ref>\n\n<gallery perrow=\"5\" mode=\"packed\" heights=\"175\">\nFile:\u0414\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0439 \u041d\u043e\u0441\u043e\u0432.jpg|{{center|former [[State Duma|Deputy]]<br />'''[[Dmitri Nossov]]'''}}\nFile:\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439 \u041f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439.jpg|{{center|former CEO of the Mirax Group<br />'''[[Sergei Polonsky]]'''{{refn|group=b|name=Polonsky}}}}\n</gallery>\n\n==Potential candidates==\nIndividuals in this section are the subject of speculation about 